## Material semantics (M3 surface foundation)

Authority order: `app/globals.css` → ADR-0001 §13 → AGENTS §7. If they diverge, `globals.css` + ADR win — fix this rule in the same change.

> The shell foundation is **Material 3 hybrid**: opaque surface roles, restrained elevation, and on-brand state colors. Glass / cognition gradients / blur tiers are **retired**. Buttons, forms, tables, and ERP content stay `opaque`. Surfaces communicate state through M3 surface containers, not blur.

### Token chain

```
--af-brand-seed (oklch)
  → --md-ref-palette-* (M3 reference palette, primary/secondary/tertiary/error/neutral)
    → --md-sys-color-* (M3 system color roles: primary, surface-container-*, on-*, outline-*)
       --md-sys-shape-corner-* / --md-sys-elevation-level* / --md-sys-motion-* / --md-sys-state-*-opacity
      → shadcn aliases (--background, --primary, --card, --sidebar-*, --chart-*)
        → Tailwind v4 @theme inline utilities (bg-card, text-primary, …)
      → --erp-* control / field / table contracts → --af-control-* (back-compat)
```

### Four phases (still the canonical state machine)

| Phase | Class | M3 mapping | When |
|---|---|---|---|
| `shell` | `.af-material-shell` | `surface-container` + `elevation-level1` | Idle, settled — default for chrome |
| `transition` | `.af-material-transition` | `surface-container-high` + `elevation-level2` | Hover / focus / typing |
| `cognition` | `.af-material-cognition` | `surface-container-highest` + `elevation-level3` + primary-tinted border | Truth resolution (Lynx active) |
| opaque | `.af-material-opaque` | `--card` flat | Dense reading surfaces — **required** for tables, ledgers, audit logs, ERP forms |

The `cognition` class name is preserved for backward compatibility with consumers; semantically it now reads as "highest opaque surface with primary-tinted border + elevation-3" — no glass, no gradient, no blur.

### `data-phase` state machine (canonical values only)

```
idle → hover → focus → typing → resolving → execution → settled
```

Forbidden ad-hoc names: `active`, `selected`, `open`, `loading`, `processing`, `ai`, `aiActive`.

### Lynx-on-M3 mapping (5 states)

`.af-material[data-lynx="…"]` rules express Lynx machine state through M3 tokens. **No new tokens. No animations.** Each rule reads as a static M3 surface + state-layer combination.

| `data-lynx` value | M3 surface role | M3 elevation / border | Meaning |
|---|---|---|---|
| `listening` | mix(`tertiary-container` 55%, `surface-container`) | tinted `outline-variant` | Awaiting input / passive intelligence |
| `resolving` | `tertiary-container` | `elevation-level2`, `tertiary` border | Active truth retrieval |
| `high-confidence` | `primary-container` | `elevation-level2`, `primary` border | Resolved with confidence |
| `warning` | (inherit) | `error` border + 1px error ring | Low confidence / data conflict |
| `mismatch` | `error-container` | `error` border | Hard mismatch / contradiction |

Banned user-facing labels: **AI mode**, **AI active**, **Thinking**, **Processing**, **Generating**. Use: `resolving`, `listening`, `high confidence`, `warning`, `mismatch`.

### Surface adoption matrix

| Surface | Allowed material |
|---|---|
| Utility bar (L1) | `shell` only (paired with `.af-nexus-l1-chrome-backplate`) |
| Dock (L4) | `shell` |
| Command palette (L3) | `shell → transition → cognition` (palette overlay blur is owned by shadcn `CommandDialog`, not by `.af-nexus-popover-panel`) |
| Lynx resolution surfaces | `.af-material[data-lynx]` (5 states above) |
| Modals, toasts | `shell` or `transition` |
| Dense tables / ledgers / audit logs | `opaque` only |
| ERP forms | `opaque` or light `shell` |

### Forbidden patterns (CI-enforced outside `app/globals.css`)

```ts
// ❌ inline style — bypasses material governance
style={{ backdropFilter: "blur(20px)" }}
style={{ willChange: "backdrop-filter" }}
```
```html
<!-- ❌ arbitrary blur — bypasses M3 surface contract -->
<div className="backdrop-blur-[18px]" />
<div className="blur-[24px]" />
<!-- ❌ scaled backdrop-blur under components/nexus/ -->
<div className="backdrop-blur-2xl" />
```
```css
/* ❌ permanent motion — cognitive fatigue */
animation: pulse 2s ease infinite;
```

Also forbidden (drift detectors — see `check-design-contract.mjs`):
- `--af-water-*`, `.af-material-water`, `.af-material-transitioning` (legacy renames)
- `--af-cognition-*`, `--af-glass-*`, `--af-resolution-*`, `--af-blur-*`, `--af-depth-*`, `--af-current-strength`, `--af-ripple-strength`, `--af-flow-angle`, `--af-material-edge`, `--af-material-highlight` (retired by M3 hybrid — express intent through `--md-sys-*` instead)
- `af-pressure-pulse`, `af-unstable-refraction` (retired Lynx animations — express via `.af-material[data-lynx]` in `app/globals.css`)
- `data-layout-density="compact|relaxed"` (CSS block removed; re-add the `:root[data-layout-density]` block before re-introducing the attribute)

### Nexus chrome utilities (`components/nexus/` only)

Use these CSS helpers — do **not** apply Tailwind `backdrop-blur-*` directly:
- `.af-nexus-l1-chrome-backplate` (L1 utility-bar surface; pair `.af-nexus-utility-bar-backdrop` on the bar)
- `.af-nexus-popover-panel` (floating panels — opaque popover surface)
- `.af-nexus-round-control-backdrop` (icon-only round controls)

These classes own the chrome surface contract. They no longer apply `backdrop-filter` (M3 surfaces are opaque); the rule still routes consumers through them so any future blur reintroduction stays centralized.

### Animation discipline

- State pulses fire **3 iterations on entry, then settle**.
- Persistent state: communicate via **static styling** (`outline`, `border-color`, M3 surface role swap), never infinite animation.
- All animations respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.
- Motion duration / easing must reference `--md-sys-motion-duration-*` / `--md-sys-motion-easing-*` (or their `--motion-*` aliases).

